cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with program synthesis and requirements engineering. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of forall-exists formulas and Skolem functions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes a compiler to translate Skolem-containing implementations to the C programming language. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as program synthesis is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with formal requirements and model checking.
